    <briefdescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext" kindref="compound">UiContext</ref> provides access to UI-related functionality and context. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext" kindref="compound">UiContext</ref> is a singleton that provides access to UI context information including the default window, render thread management, idle callbacks, and application locale settings.</para>
<para>Usage example: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext_1af743ec0de32da4605b719915fefeef4f" kindref="member">UiContext</ref><sp/>context<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext_1aaf4d5ae8fc614b7ac997a63477c2599b" kindref="member">UiContext::Get</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1Window" kindref="compound">Dali::Window</ref><sp/>window<sp/>=<sp/>context.GetDefaultWindow();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Use<sp/>window<sp/>and<sp/>context<sp/>for<sp/>UI<sp/>operations</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext" kindref="compound">UiContext</ref> is a singleton - use <ref refid="classDali_1_1UiContext_1aaf4d5ae8fc614b7ac997a63477c2599b" kindref="member">Get()</ref> to retrieve the instance @SINCE_2_5.10 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
